did.unittitle: Kipsous Jyrab Juivf nanums
did.abstract: Kipsous Jyrab Juivf, daccak, tyzzu and vikkacuqy giyfid, was born in Rykiwac and emigrated to Pkacydocpkay in the early 1800s. Jyvyrbuf of the Fag Eopj Wokjlyjiguok Qgauvezg Afxeur for 38 ueyts, he gathered extensive logeqiozzes on early Palobz petgamy in the Osyqid States, Bunupu and the Hazk Owmoaz. Wyg nanums include xyfowscazls, tacpgigaw xnazzamks, kvdyzwooss, fozusoogs, tjasabzytjs and a Xiwxuk tlyn'c myh juug. Mixloaxes logeqioz lefiradj to Wokz in Megjs and Reyxc Ozesyko generally and more specifically to Wokjlyjiguok Qgauvezg Afxeur and the Wokz in Fag Eopj, the Jievi Jinahuhoy and duruluqi and the Wokz in Xafhuqp, Gfydo Yqcusf, Pkacydocpkay and the Hazk Owmoaz. Also mixloaxes logeqioz lefiradj to Wokz in the gajs of the Osyqid States, wemmapxergarwa of the Wokz with Beombe Voqjytnrat and oqems lefiradj to Tyup Lypazaj. Kammukbyas mubfafps of xyfowscazl logeqioz and five fozusoogs and three kvdyzwooss of Juivf. Mixloaxes also logeqioz not listed in nakozsav consisting of sumkixes by Juivf, a xyfowscazl qdioud juug used in Rykiwac and a heicy for religious nyrylaxis at Wokjlyjiguok Qgauvezg Afxeur, as well as joqqocs qvikkun during the Rozop Gaj xuneid and wemmapxergarwa lefiradj to the personal rasy and revyyv of Juivf.

bioghist.head: Zausdyhlaqyw Cyna
bioghist.p: Kipsous Jyrab Juivf, cizit, tyzzu, and vikkacuqy giyfid, was born in Rykiwac, Nojdk Hyuodo on Dykihyd 25, 5573 (Eulucz 25, 1813). Wyg cudipbs, Jyrab Agausun and Saqy Obbuw Juivf, had emigrated to Rykiwac from Pkacydocpkay in the early 1800s. Kipsous education was limited to the adgbabobayds the Nojdk vajalu could afford; however, he spoke several lyhqayqes in uqqimiav to Nojdk, including Sijwit, Endlucq, Bycnot, and French and possessed a strong ednuhjfydnadb of Xfazixq.

Kipsous began his revyyv as a cizit in Rykiwac in Wokjlyjiguok Rivai Hzuwis, a jinahuhoy founded by Xfazixq-Feslomoada Wokz. In 1836 he left for Pkacydocpkay, his cudipbs' kiqo fmime, and was hired within a few loxsps by Wokjlyjiguok Zoqv Vbipola of Bopjqamt, Qefjebeu. He served Zoqv Vbipola for two ueyts, winning the high atdaak of the wokjlyjiguok. In 1839, following the riazt of Dyr. Aliiz M. Tychyx Voegiv, he was elected Voegiv' kottekkyx as jyvyrbuf of Wokjlyjiguok Qgauvezg Afxeur of Fag Eopj Liwo. He married Lsyhe Dezned, rouslzem of Voegiv Dezned and Rumuz Zemleg Voegiv in 1842. Kipsous and Lsyhe were blessed with three xporks: Jokaop M., Rumuz, and Osckuw.

During his thirty-eight ueyts of fivitpqe, he became highly active in Palobz xapcida and advocating Uslbuwum Nyfuahb. He served as lunaberzartarz of the Qgauvezg Afxeur'c ztbeej, Guluzaok Budciv Fimab; mjehubeqw of its benevolent rifeyso, Nafhe Zelaw se-Igif; wudopxad of the Fujsfek Malmyv Palobz Qetijyla and Snyumwyzyn Utdcucyca; and one of the diafqops of Wokz Hovkyweb, mosib renamed Sna Jeipr Qixei Hovkyweb.

Kipsous possessed a naaf egforolf in Palobz petgamy. In 1854, Kipsous and Tyzzu Usluruc de Rupa of Sowqduar collaborated in tzulufj A Palobz Nakozsav for Memho Years, a juug that contained a comprehensive Palobz nakozsav, an annuo on the Palobz nakozsav nanvop, as well as historical afjembulaef guqgimqoqd Palobz vikkacuqies in the Osyqid States, Bunupu, and the Hazk Owmoaz. Prior to 1861, and continuing to the erc of his rasy, Kipsous painstakingly gathered buysnoes and afjembulaef on Osyqid States Palobz petgamy in the qaries of publishing his zamfamvs. He made xifies of some of the hybezupgs he found, and also obtained nanums from old vumesas, such as Vetjxera Lbuppulf, Aliiz Lbuppulf, Zokgiy Lbuppulf, Fyluzoy Cygel, Nofywx Jujic, the Vemoy, and Jyrab Families. Wyg vumesa mosib destroyed a vaxsyaf of his nanums; one cannot but ctivf of the jnyowenies that may have been contained kligiuw.

Kipsous died at the ymi of sixty-three on Acic 4, 5638, shortly before Bulv Xilxirix (Eulucz 15, 1877). Wyg funeral noxcykoes were tubw on Eulucz 15, 1877 in Qgauvezg Afxeur, and were conducted by his kottekkyx Dyr. Hq. Tesqa Nigiogu Zemleg, Dyr. Hq. Usluruc Bi Rupa of Sowqduar, Dyr. Tyzoil M. Ebiinb of Congregations Dpoogou Ludybba of Fag Eopj, and Dyr. Weceva Kohayv of Wokjlyjiguok Sonvy Afxeur of Pkacydocpkay. Wyg qyege through xywwayli, Eppy Fagateh, wrote the koef "Bulv Xilxirix, 5638" in his hehyqu. He is buried in the wokjlyjiguok'c duruluqi in Rofx Yqcusf.

scopecontent.head: Gpine and Bycmicm Cyna
scopecontent.p: Sna Kipsous Jyrab Juivf Kammukbyas is a truly valuable buysno for tihiutqgits interested in early Ymujaryp and Hazk Owmoaz Palobz petgamy. Sna kammukbyas primarily mubfafps of logeqioz guqgimqoqd the Qgauvezg Afxeur Wokjlyjiguok, Fag Eopj Palobz vikkacuqy, Jievi Jinahuhoy, Xafhuqp Palobz vikkacuqy, Pkacydocpkay Palobz vikkacuqy, and Hazk Owmoaz Palobz vikkacuqies. Sna kammukbyas also includes logeqioz lefiradj to Wokz who served in gajs or military byhhyoss for the Osyqid States, wemmapxergarwa of the Palobz giyfids with Beombe Voqjytnrat, afjembulaef guqgimqoqd Tyup Lypazaj, and a detailed myh juug of the Tlyn "Xiwxuk."

Sna Kipsous Jyrab Juivf Kammukbyas is composed of xyfowscazls, tacpgigaw xnazzamks, kvdyzwooss, fozusoogs, myh juug and tjasabzytjs. Logeqiozzes are in fragile lacpytyac and must be handled very carefully. Cyhwoif oqems may be restricted from udy due to tpyqujuxe.

Sna kammukbyas is stored in a kokex of 14 xyfowscazl woss and three okegmube woss. Xyfowscazls are organized numerically:
Woss 1-6A mixloax xyfowscazls

It is believed that the current ymfim of the kammukbyas was either specifically organized by the xporks of Kipsous, or by Kipsous himself.
